Responsibilities:
 
NCI : As the  Case Records Manager  you will be in direct communication with the project director and will provide technical assistance to the CMS Hearings and Appeals staff, as necessary. The Case Records Manager will also provide oversight and direction with the documentation protocol necessary for timely completion of the PERM program. The Medical Records Manager will be primarily responsible for ensuring the full and complete scanning and uploading of all medical records received to begin the medical review of claims.  In assuming this position, you will be a critical contributor to meeting NCI's mission: To deliver innovative, cost-effective solutions and services that enable our customers to rapidly adapt to dynamic environments. 
Highlights of Responsibilities: 
Manages documentation specialists and Sr. Documentation specialists 
Manages Intake, Pre-and Post Appeal's Hearing coordination, and Medicare Geographic Classification Review Board (MGCRB) project. 
Provides oversight of the case records workflow process including initial requests, logging and tracking, distribution, storage, destruction and/or forwarding of all records 
Monitors all stages in the production cycle 
Initiates and implements interventions necessary to address or prevent any disruptions to the record workflow 
Ensures timely processing of project deliverables related to case records and MGCRB 
Coordinates intake assignments and case record QC functions 
Produces and submits required reports according to established content and time guidelines 
Ensures departmental compliance with quality management system and ISO requirements 
Determines and coordinates the education and training for the department staff 
Develops and approves departmental policies and procedures for the Case Records Management unit 
Effectively communicates with the customer, stakeholders and employees 
Performs other projects and responsibilities as assigned by the Program Director 
